<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Kanban Board - basic authentication</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta http-equiv="x-ua-compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
  </head>

  <body>
    <nav class="navbar navbar-light mb-1" style="background-color: #e3f2fd;">
      <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">
        <%= image_tag('logo.svg', size: "30x30", alt: "Kanban Boards", class: 'd-inline-block') %>
        Kanban Boards
      </a>
      <span class="navbar-text float-xs-left mr-1">
          Four Demo Apps for Login: 
      </span>
      <ul class="nav navbar-nav">      
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link" 
             href="https://kanban-1.herokuapp.com/">No Login</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item active">
          <a class="nav-link" 
             href="https://kanban-2.herokuapp.com/">basic authentication 
             <span class="sr-only">(current)</span></a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link" 
             href="https://kanban-3.herokuapp.com/">devise</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link" 
             href="https://kanban-4.herokuapp.com/">omniauth</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <span class="navbar-text float-xs-right">
        <% if current_user.nil? %>
          <%= link_to 'login', '/login' %>
            |
          <%= link_to "register", new_user_path %>
        <% else %>
          <%= link_to "logout #{current_user.username}", '/logout' %>
        <% end %>
      </span>
    </nav>    
    <div class="container">
      <% flash.each do |key, value| %>
          <div class="alert alert-info mt-1"><strong><%= key %>:</strong> <%= value %></div>
      <% end %>

      <%= yield %>
    </div>
    <footer class="bd-footer text-muted">
      <div class="container">
        <p>This Demo App offers basic authentication with <kbd>has_secure_password</kbd> in the
          user model, and a session controller for login and logout. The id of the current
          user is stored in the session. Rails uses the session-cookie <kbd><%=
        Rails.application.config.session_options[:key] %></kbd> automatically.</p>
        <p>Try logging in as user <kbd>mariam</kbd> with password <kbd>badpassword123</kbd>.</p>
        <p>You can find the source code in branch
          <kbd>basic_auth</kbd> of <a href="https://github.com/backend-development/rails-example-kanban-board-login">the repository</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
